.TH "ibmvnic_wait_for_completion" 9 "ibmvnic_wait_for_completion" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ibmvnic_wait_for_completion \- Check device state and wait for completion
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ibmvnic_wait_for_completion
.BI "(struct ibmvnic_adapter *adapter "  ","
.BI "struct completion *comp_done "  ","
.BI "unsigned long timeout "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adapter" 12
private device data
.IP "comp_done" 12
completion structure to wait for
.IP "timeout" 12
time to wait in milliseconds
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Wait for a completion signal or until the timeout limit is reached
while checking that the device is still active.
